            <summary><p>1 fol. on parchment; Sold on 22 April 2015 as Lot 62;  Qurʾānic Text: Q 4:12-4:17; 15 lines per page; Dimensions: appr. 370 x 290mm; Script style: kūfī D; Estimated date of production: 800-1000.</p><p> </p><p>For a detailed catalogue entry about the Blue Qurʾān, including a large  list of sister fragments scattered in collections around the world, see  entry <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/2/vers/286?handschrift=1458">HC.MS.03223</ref> (written by Marcus Fraser). Some of the metadata was carried over from that manuscript.</p><p> </p>Further information can also be found on <ref target="https://www.sothebys.com/en/auctions/ecatalogue/2015/arts-islamic-world-l15220/lot.62.html?locale=en">Sotheby's website</ref>.<p/></summary>
